          MODULE=cowsay
         VERSION=3.03
          SOURCE=$MODULE-$VERSION.tar.gz
SOURCE_DIRECTORY=$BUILD_DIRECTORY/$MODULE-$VERSION
   SOURCE_URL[0]=http://www.nog.net/~tony/warez/$SOURCE
        WEB_SITE=http://www.nog.net/~tony/warez/cowsay.shtml
         ENTERED=20020221
         UPDATED=20020221
           SHORT="A Configurable Speaking/Thinking Cow"
cat << EOF
Cowsay is basically a text filter. Send some text into it, and you get 
a cow saying your text. Very easy to use, I would hope. All you need is 
a working installation of Perl 5. And if you think a talking cow isn't 
enough, cows can think too. All you have to do is run cowthink.
EOF

